<h1>Volunteer With Get Connected</h1>
<p>Since its inception in 2000, more than 5,000 students have volunteered with the Get Connected program. Volunteers are needed for our three major programs: I-Reps, I-Teams, and I-Night.</p>
<h2>I-Reps</h2>
<ul>
<li>I-Reps greet students and parents as they come to campus and to Rexburg.</li>
<li>I-Reps oversee Get Connected registration and provide answers to commonly asked questions during Move-in Day and Get Connected.</li>
<li>I-Reps have opportunities to serve incoming students and parents one-by-one.</li>
<li>I-Reps assist with the Get Connected events.</li>
<li>I-Reps serve in I-Rep Groups and get to have fun while working closely with one another.</li>
</ul>
<h2>I-Team Leaders</h2>
<ul>
<li>I-Team Leaders are paired together and oversee an I-Team group of new students.</li>
<li>I-Team Leaders have opportunities to teach and share their personal feelings and experiences about BYUI with their I-Team group as they participate in the various events sponsored during Get Connected.</li>
</ul>
<h2>I-Night Volunteers</h2>
<ul>
<li>I-Night is the back-to-school start of the semester bash for all new and current students.</li>
<li>More than 100 volunteers are needed to staff the event.</li>
<li>Volunteers receive free admission to the event but are required to work two of the four hours of the event.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Application Process</h2>
<h3>Step 1:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">Send an e-mail to <a href="mailto: getconnected@byui.edu">getconnected@byui.edu</a> with your name, BYUI e-mail address, preferred e-mail address, cell phone number, cell provider, and your typed authorization (yes or no) to send you text messages.</p>
<h3>Step 2:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">You will receive e-mail and/or text message reminders about upcoming interviews.</p>
<h3>Step 3:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">Attend an volunteer interview and sign the volunteer contract. If you are off-track and away from Rexburg, please contact us so we can setup a phone interview with you.</p>
<h3>Step 4:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">Placement decisions are made each Wednesday following interviews. You will be notified via e-mail whether or not you have been placed.</p>
<h3>Step 5:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">You will have 48 hours to reject your offer before your volunteer contract is enforced.</p>
<h3>Step 6:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">Attend the mandatory Spirit Conference training for all Get Connected volunteers.</p>
<h3>Step 7:</h3>
<p style="padding-left: 15px;">Participate in Get Connected and enjoy serving the new students coming to BYUI.</p>
